Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
As exclusive agent for Akron Innovation Campus LLC, CBRE, Inc., is pleased to present to qualified investors the opportunity to acquire The Akron Innovation Campus (“AIC”) located at 411 (“411”) & 441 (“441”) Wolf Ledges Parkway in Akron, OH (“Properties”). This two-building office campus is in the Akron submarket, and is a part of a designated Opportunity Zone and HUBZone. Built in 1970 and 1980, respectively, the properties have been owned by the University of Akron Research Foundation since 2007 and managed by CBRE Property Management.

The properties have undergone extensive building upgrades with a million dollars spent from ownership on upgrades to building systems and owner contributed tenant improvements. Notable improvements and upgrades include brand new roofs and HVAC systems at both properties, as well as elevator and outdoor lighting upgrades. New ownership will have a rare-opportunity to increase value via raising below-market rents, increasing occupancy, and investing in interior improvements and upgrades.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer for sale 6500 New Albany Road, a two (2) story office campus in Columbus’s premier suburban submarket (New Albany). The property was developed in 1998 as a single-tenant Property for Discover Financial Services, and encompasses approximately 333,169 rentable square feet on 51.7 acres.  The Property was the foundational building block to the now 4,000+ acre Business Park, home to the region’s and nation’s leading operation centers.

Constructed with three pods, the north and south pods are two stories, and the center pod houses support areas for the buildings such as a cafeteria, fitness center and a data center. The site has diverse fiber with multiple network carrier and dual electric feeds are available to the site. 

The asset is owned and currently occupied by Discover Financial Group and is being offered as a vacant acquisition opportunity.  Discover will consider a sale-leaseback transaction structure with a shorter-term leasehold interest.
